          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Being a part of Shigally Hill International Academy Girl’s Residential School, I strongly recommend it to all those looking for Residential School in Uttrakhand for their girl child. Their curriculum is excellent with a good balance of academics, co-curricular activities and discipline. The teachers and other staff are very helpful and take care of children as their own, because of which the child feels at home.The appropriate place for study. Creative thoughts start to grow from schools, though it depends on the environment. This beautiful natural environment is appropriate to develop a simple brain to a creative one. Even only nature could produce real human beings which is really lacking in today's life.\nOur Indian history says about Vedic age, at that time students used to go to Ashrama for appropriate study living in nature.Definitely a good school for girls.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
