          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Had a horrible experience. My child couldn't even stay there for 10 days. Apart from the picturesque scenery nothing is right. Surely, everything looks picture perfect to new commers and their parents at the time of admission however the reality can't be far from the truth. Students are not at all cordial and friendly towards new-commers. And these aren't the problem faced by my child alone but by many others. My child was extremely disheartened and depressed after join this school in just 10 days and when i brought this to the attention of the concerned faculty no measures were taken. Several lies were told at the time of admission. Keeping this comment short and crisp, i would just ask parents to do their due diligence before sending their beloved children to any school rather than seeing every thing from rose-tinted glasses that the school offers initially.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
